/-
`filter_upwards [h‚āĀ, ‚čĮ, h‚āô]` replaces a goal of the form `s ‚ąą f` and terms
`h‚āĀ : t‚āĀ ‚ąą f, ‚čĮ, h‚āô : t‚āô ‚ąą f` with `‚ąÄ x, x ‚ąą t‚āĀ ‚Üí ‚čĮ ‚Üí x ‚ąą t‚āô ‚Üí x ‚ąą s`.
The list is an optional parameter, `[]` being its default value.

`filter_upwards [h‚āĀ, ‚čĮ, h‚āô] with a‚āĀ a‚āā ‚čĮ a‚āĖ` is a short form for
`{ filter_upwards [h‚āĀ, ‚čĮ, h‚āô], intro a‚āĀ a‚āā ‚čĮ a‚āĖ }`.

`filter_upwards [h‚āĀ, ‚čĮ, h‚āô] using e` is a short form for
`{ filter_upwards [h1, ‚čĮ, hn], exact e }`.

Combining both shortcuts is done by writing `filter_upwards [h‚āĀ, ‚čĮ, h‚āô] with a‚āĀ a‚āā ‚čĮ a‚āĖ using e`.
Note that in this case, the `aŠĶĘ` terms can be used in `e`.
-/

example [TopologicalSpace őĪ] {x : őĪ} {p p' q q' : őĪ ‚Üí Prop}
    (hT : {x | p x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x)
    (hT' : {x | p' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x)
    (hS : {x | q x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x)
    (hS' : {x | q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x) :
    {x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := by
  have h‚āĀ : {x | p x ‚ąß q x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := by
    have h‚āā : {x | p x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := hT
    have h‚āÉ : {x | q x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := hS
    have h‚āĄ : {x | p x ‚ąß q x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := by
      -- Use the fact that the intersection of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood
      have h‚āÖ : {x | p x ‚ąß q x} = {x | p x} ‚ą© {x | q x} := by
        ext x
        simp [and_comm]
        <;> aesop
      rw [h‚āÖ]
      -- Use the fact that the intersection of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood
      exact mem_nhds_inter h‚āā h‚āÉ
    exact h‚āĄ
  have h‚āā : {x | p' x ‚ąß q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := by
    have h‚āÉ : {x | p' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := hT'
    have h‚āĄ : {x | q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := hS'
    have h‚āÖ : {x | p' x ‚ąß q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := by
      -- Use the fact that the intersection of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood
      have h‚āÜ : {x | p' x ‚ąß q' x} = {x | p' x} ‚ą© {x | q' x} := by
        ext x
        simp [and_comm]
        <;> aesop
      rw [h‚āÜ]
      -- Use the fact that the intersection of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood
      exact mem_nhds_inter h‚āÉ h‚āĄ
    exact h‚āÖ
  -- Use the fact that the union of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood
  have h‚āÉ : {x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x := by
    have h‚āĄ : {x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x} = {x | p x ‚ąß q x} ‚ą™ {x | p' x ‚ąß q' x} := by
      ext x
      simp [or_comm]
      <;> aesop
    rw [h‚āĄ]
    -- Use the fact that the union of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood
    exact mem_nhds_union h‚āĀ h‚āā
  exact h‚āÉ

